title.rendered: UP vs Delhi, India Women’s League 2023: Fantasy Cricket Tips

content.rendered:
We have opted for a fantasy cricket team based on the recent performances, overall impact, and credit points.

Probable XIs

UP: Devika Vaidya, Alyssa Healy (c & wk), Kiran Navgire, Tahlia McGrath, Grace Harris, Deepti Sharma, Sophie Ecclestone, Simran Shaikh, Anjali Sarvani, Parshavi Chopra, Rajeshwari Gayakwad

Delhi: Meg Lanning (c), Shafali Verma, Alice Capsey, Jemimah Rodrigues, Marizanne Kapp, Taniya Bhatia (wk), Jess Jonassen, Radha Yadav, Arundhati Reddy, Shikha Pandey, Poonam Yadav

Also Read:

South Africa vs West Indies, 1st T20I: Fantasy Tips

Pitch Report

Venue: Brabourne Stadium, Mumbai

(Based on the last three games)

1st innings average score: 171

2nd innings average score: 187

Wickets per innings: 5

Type: Good for batting

Wins

Batting 1st: 33%

Batting 2nd: 67%

Fantasy Tips of The Day

After three visits to the Brabourne Stadium this season, Alyssa Healy averages a whopping 83, including the highest score of 96*.

Besides picking nine wickets, Marizanne Kapp has generated bonus points for crossing the 30-run mark on three occasions – of which two came at the very venue.

Sophie Ecclestone is yet to go wicketless and is the highest wicket-taker (13) in the tournament. Given her wicket-taking ability, she has featured in the Best11 in all the games.

By going all guns blazing (170 strike rate), Grace Harris has helped fantasy players march ahead. In only four innings, she has collected 216 runs at a staggering average of 72.

Meg Lanning is the leading run-getter in this edition (271 at 54). Her highest score (72) of the season came at the Brabourne Stadium.

It has been a decent start to the year for Parshavi Chopra, who has picked 15 wickets in her last 10 competitive T20s.

Radha Yadav hasn’t been very productive with the ball but has made amends by taking the most catches (six) in the competition, including three in the match against UP.

When these teams locked horns earlier in the league. Tahlia McGrath (90 runs and a wicket) and Jess Jonassen (42 runs and three wickets) were the captain and vice-captain of the Best11 respectively.

Poonam Yadav has struggled with the ball lately, managing only five wickets in her last 10 white-ball outings.
